t), l'ordre d'apparition des données est tout aussi important que les données elles-mêmes.*"],"metadata":{"id":"Y0LG439By99F"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# 1. Sort by order_id to ensure the chronological sequence of the data stream\n","df = df.sort_values(by='order_id').reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","# 2. Define the administrative columns to drop\n","admin_cols = ['teacher_id', 'school_id', 'student_class_id']\n","\n","# 3. Retain only the 17 target features\n","df_17 = df.drop(columns=admin_cols)\n","\n","print(f\"Shape after filtering: {df_17.shape}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"uES6YfmnxwEY","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008571350,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":138,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"a588d617-4fd6-4a40-edd4-a75a87f1edff"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Shape after filtering: (500000, 17)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 3 : Diagnostic des données brutes**"],"metadata":{"id":"tu0n_6InsZxn"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ce code effectue un diagnostic de santé de vos données. Il compte les informations manquantes pour les compétences et le temps de réponse, tout en testant si les scores des étudiants peuvent être transformés en simples 0 (échec) ou 1 (réussite)."],"metadata":{"id":"7Y60prnM8hZ2"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Le grand coupable : list_skills (301 330 lignes perdues !)**\n","Puisque notre objectif est d'expliquer l'adaptation des modèles à la dérive conceptuelle, nous avons effectivement besoin de connaître le concept (la compétence) pour analyser sa dérive. Supprimer ces lignes est donc techniquement justifiable, même si la perte est énorme. L'alternative serait de remplacer les NaN par une catégorie \"Skill_Inconnu\", mais *cela risque de créer un \"concept\" artificiel très bruité qui n'aidera pas notre modèle d'apprentissage continu.*"],"metadata":{"id":"MzkKf9UCsyjU"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**Le temps de réponse (123 lignes perdues)**\n","Seulement 123 lignes ont été supprimées à cause d'un temps de réponse manquant ou invalide. C'est négligeable sur un volume de 500 000 lignes, notre approche avec errors='coerce' et dropna est donc tout à fait appropriée ici."],"metadata":{"id":"zt3NPuZtudoR"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# 1. Count missing values in the 'list_skills' feature\n","print(\"Missing values in list_skills:\", df_17['list_skills'].isna().sum())\n","\n","# 2. Diagnostic of the strict binarization on the 'correct' target\n","print(\"\\nSimulation of 'correct' values after strict binarization:\")\n","simulation_correct = (df_17['correct'] == 1.0).astype(int)\n","print(simulation_correct.value_counts(dropna=False))\n","\n","# 3. Count missing values in response times\n","print(\"\\nMissing values in response time:\", df_17['ms_first_response_time'].isna().sum())"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Dee2li71rVkL","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008571456,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":89,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"b8236c88-a156-473a-f9be-d60c4be17879"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Missing values in list_skills: 301330\n","\n","Simulation of 'correct' values after strict binarization:\n","correct\n","1    308050\n","0    191950\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n","\n","Missing values in response time: 123\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Étape 4 : Nettoyage Rigoureux (Missing Values & Consistency)**"],"metadata":{"id":"unVG0TSgy1zC"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["*C'est ici que l'on s'assure que le modèle ne va pas \"planter\" ou apprendre sur du vide. Pour nos recherches sur l'XAI (Explicabilité), avoir des étiquettes de compétences propres est indispensable.*"],"metadata":{"id":"iAfBfujpzBLI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# A. Processing 'list_skills' (Knowledge Components)\n","# Drop rows with missing skills and explicitly CREATE A COPY to prevent SettingWithCopyWarning\n","df_clean = df_17.dropna(subset=['list_skills']).copy()\n","\n","# B. Processing the 'correct' target: Strict binarization\n","# Only a perfect score of 1.0 maps to 1, any partial or incorrect score maps to 0\n","df_clean['correct'] = (df_clean['correct'] == 1.0).astype(int)\n","\n","# C. Type conversion and cleaning for response time\n","df_clean['ms_first_response_time'] = pd.to_numeric(df_clean['ms_first_response_time'], errors='coerce')\n","df_clean = df_clean.dropna(subset=['ms_first_response_time'])\n","\n","# Data Health Verification (Sanity Check)\n","print(f\"Initial rows: {len(df_17)}\")\n","print(f\"Rows after cleaning: {len(df_clean)}\")\n","print(f\"Percentage retained: {(len(df_clean)/len(df_17))*100:.2f}%\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"hprbtBEDy4Et","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008571618,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":158,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"47a5ad09-c837-4dde-d9a7-828badcd30a6"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Initial rows: 500000\n","Rows after cleaning: 198662\n","Percentage retained: 39.73%\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Étape 5 : Sequential Feature Engineering (Historical Context)**"],"metadata":{"id":"6pshbe0SrGJg"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["La création  de nouveaux indicateurs permet de mesurer l'évolution de chaque étudiant. Il calcule automatiquement :\n","\n","\n","*   nombre de tentatives passées\n","*   son taux de réussite historique\n","*   son score de gamification (points gagnés ou perdus)\n","\n","\n","Toutes ces données sont calculées de manière à\n","ce que l'IA ne puisse pas \"tricher\" en voyant le futur."],"metadata":{"id":"LVajOzGc-Dp7"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","# 1. Ensure strict chronological order before sequential calculations\n","df_clean = df_clean.sort_values(by='order_id').reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","# 2. Calculate past attempts for each user on each specific skill\n","df_clean['past_attempts'] = df_clean.groupby(['user_id', 'list_skills']).cumcount()\n","\n","# 3. Calculate past successes strictly avoiding data leakage\n","# (Subtracting the current row's 'correct' value ensures the model doesn't see the future)\n","cumulative_success = df_clean.groupby(['user_id', 'list_skills'])['correct'].cumsum()\n","df_clean['past_successes'] = cumulative_success - df_clean['correct']\n","\n","# 4. Calculate historical accuracy (handling division by zero for the first attempt)\n","df_clean['historical_accuracy'] = np.where(\n","    df_clean['past_attempts'] > 0,\n","    df_clean['past_successes'] / df_clean['past_attempts'],\n","    0.0\n",")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 5. GAMIFICATION CONCEPT INTEGRATION\n","# ==========================================\n","# Define gamification rules (rewards and penalties)\n","REWARD_POINTS = 10\n","PENALTY_POINTS = -5\n","\n","# Assign points earned or lost for each interaction\n","df_clean['points_earned'] = np.where(df_clean['correct'] == 1, REWARD_POINTS, PENALTY_POINTS)\n","\n","# Calculate cumulative score strictly avoiding data leakage\n","# Note: No need to re-sort by user_id here. The global chronological sort from Step 1 is preserved,\n","# and pandas groupby cumsum() handles user-specific accumulation automatically.\n","cumulative_score = df_clean.groupby('user_id')['points_earned'].cumsum()\n","\n","# Subtract the current row's points to ensure the score represents the strictly past state\n","df_clean['gamification_score'] = cumulative_score - df_clean['points_earned']\n","\n","# Optional: Prevent the score from dropping below zero (common in gamification)\n","# df_clean['gamification_score'] = df_clean['gamification_score'].clip(lower=0)\n","\n","# Clean up: drop the temporary column\n","df_clean = df_clean.drop(columns=['points_earned'])\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 5.BIS: GAMIFICATION - MAGIC HINTS (FOR SUBJECT 2 XAI)\n","# ==========================================\n","# Simulating the use of hints logically based on the student's effort\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","def generate_magic_hints(row):\n","    if row['correct'] == 1 and row['past_attempts'] == 0:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1], p=[0.90, 0.10]) # Quick success = rarely uses a hint\n","    elif row['correct'] == 1 and row['past_attempts'] > 0:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1, 2], p=[0.20, 0.50, 0.30]) # Success after effort = likely used hints\n","    else:\n","        return np.random.choice([0, 1, 2, 3], p=[0.30, 0.20, 0.30, 0.20]) # Failure = stuck or gave up\n","\n","df_clean['magic_hint_count'] = df_clean.apply(generate_magic_hints, axis=1)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 6. DATA TYPES IDENTIFICATION PHASE\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"--- Data Types Identification ---\")\n","print(df_clean.dtypes)\n","print(\"---------------------------------\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 7. SAVE TO GOOGLE DRIVE\n","# ==========================================\n","output_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_engineered.csv'\n","df_clean.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n","\n","# 8. Sanity check: Display the new temporal features including gamification\n","print(\"\\nSanity Check - Engineered Features:\")\n","columns_to_show = ['user_id', 'list_skills', 'correct', 'past_attempts', 'historical_accuracy', 'gamification_score']\n","print(df_clean[columns_to_show].head(10))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"ZejHkSPOrqNu","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008598041,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":26415,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"bee3587d-19f8-43c6-e6fa-2b0c40a7cceb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["--- Data Types Identification ---\n","order_id                    int64\n","assignment_id               int64\n","user_id                     int64\n","assistment_id               int64\n","problem_id                  int64\n","original                    int64\n","correct                     int64\n","attempt_count               int64\n","ms_first_response_time    float64\n","tutor_mode                 object\n","answer_type                object\n","sequence_id                 int64\n","position                    int64\n","problem_set_type           object\n","base_sequence_id            int64\n","list_skill_ids             object\n","list_skills                object\n","past_attempts               int64\n","past_successes              int64\n","historical_accuracy       float64\n","gamification_score          int64\n","magic_hint_count            int64\n","dtype: object\n","---------------------------------\n","\n","Sanity Check - Engineered Features:\n","   user_id                           list_skills  correct  past_attempts  \\\n","0    78068                            Mean;Table        0              0   \n","1    63205  Multiplication and Division Integers        1              0   \n","2    70759                  Probability Compound        0              0   \n","3    70759                  Probability Compound        0              1   \n","4    70759                  Probability Compound        1              2   \n","5    70759                  Probability Compound        1              3   \n","6    70759                  Probability Compound        1              4   \n","7    70759                          Median;Table        0              0   \n","8    70759                          Median;Table        1              1   \n","9    70759                          Median;Table        1              2   \n","\n","   historical_accuracy  gamification_score  \n","0             0.000000                   0  \n","1             0.000000                   0  \n","2             0.000000                   0  \n","3             0.000000                  -5  \n","4             0.000000                 -10  \n","5             0.333333                   0  \n","6             0.500000                  10  \n","7             0.000000                  20  \n","8             0.000000                  15  \n","9             0.500000                  25  \n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Analyse de l'évolution du système; Il calcule automatiquement la difficulté de chaque exercice en fonction des échecs passés des autres élèves, puis transforme les catégories de texte (comme le type de réponse) en formats numériques compréhensibles par la machine."],"metadata":{"id":"7YJhq5dwAF9D"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","# A. Dynamic Item Difficulty (Strictly avoiding data leakage)\n","# 1. Count global past attempts for the specific problem\n","df_clean['problem_attempts'] = df_clean.groupby('problem_id').cumcount()\n","\n","# 2. Calculate cumulative correct answers globally (excluding current row)\n","cumulative_problem_success = df_clean.groupby('problem_id')['correct'].cumsum()\n","df_clean['problem_past_success'] = cumulative_problem_success - df_clean['correct']\n","\n","# 3. Calculate dynamic difficulty: 1 - (past_success / past_attempts)\n","# Higher value = harder problem. Default to 0.5 for the very first encounter.\n","df_clean['item_difficulty'] = np.where(\n","    df_clean['problem_attempts'] > 0,\n","    1 - (df_clean['problem_past_success'] / df_clean['problem_attempts']),\n","    0.5\n",")\n","\n","# B. XAI Preparation: One-Hot Encoding for your specific categorical features\n","# We select the textual features from your list of 17\n","categorical_cols = ['tutor_mode', 'answer_type', 'problem_set_type', 'original']\n","\n","# Apply One-Hot Encoding\n","# drop_first=True is essential to avoid the dummy variable trap in XAI analysis\n","df_clean = pd.get_dummies(df_clean, columns=categorical_cols, drop_first=True, dtype=int)\n","\n","# C. Cleanup CORRIGÉ (On garde list_skills pour l'injection de dérive plus tard)\n","columns_to_drop = ['problem_attempts', 'problem_past_success', 'list_skill_ids']\n","df_final = df_clean.drop(columns=[col for col in columns_to_drop if col in df_clean.columns])\n","\n","# D. Save the final engineered dataset ready for XAI and Drift analysis\n","output_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_engineered_final.csv'\n","df_final.to_csv(output_path, index=False)\n","\n","# E. Sanity Check\n","print(\"Feature Engineering & XAI Prep Completed Successfully.\")\n","print(f\"Final shape: {df_final.shape}\")\n","print(\"\\nNew columns created (sample):\")\n","print([col for col in df_final.columns if 'answer_type' in col or 'item_difficulty' in col][:5])"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"hUkt4sqR2MND","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008603154,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":5141,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"81e1ff59-9b8b-437d-e85c-9f36812b3fdb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Feature Engineering & XAI Prep Completed Successfully.\n","Final shape: (198662, 27)\n","\n","New columns created (sample):\n","['item_difficulty', 'answer_type_choose_1', 'answer_type_fill_in_1', 'answer_type_open_response']\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## ** Etape 6 :Normalisation des données (Feature Scaling)**"],"metadata":{"id":"deVGhjOf2mS8"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Cette normalisant, nous permettons à l'algorithme d'XAI (SHAP) de comparer \"équitablement\" l'impact d'une seconde supplémentaire de réflexion avec l'impact d'un échec passé. Sans cela, le modèle pourrait accorder une importance démesurée au temps de réponse simplement parce que ses valeurs numériques sont plus grandes."],"metadata":{"id":"Hlk61rGNKUh4"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n","\n","# 1. Identify the numerical continuous features to scale\n","# We exclude IDs and binary/one-hot encoded columns\n","continuous_features = [\n","    'ms_first_response_time',\n","    'past_attempts',\n","    'past_successes',\n","    'historical_accuracy',\n","    'item_difficulty',\n","    'gamification_score', # <--- AJOUT DU SCORE DE GAMIFICATION ICI\n","    'magic_hint_count'\n","]\n","\n","# 2. Initialize the StandardScaler\n","scaler = StandardScaler()\n","\n","# 3. Apply the scaling to the continuous features\n","# We fit and transform the data in one step\n","df_final[continuous_features] = scaler.fit_transform(df_final[continuous_features])\n","\n","# 4. Final Data Integrity Check\n","print(\"Data Normalization Complete.\")\n","print(\"\\nMean and Standard Deviation after scaling (should be ~0 and ~1):\")\n","for feat in continuous_features:\n","    print(f\"{feat.ljust(25)} | Mean: {df_final[feat].mean():.2f} | Std: {df_final[feat].std():.2f}\")\n","\n","# 5. Save the final processed dataset for the modeling phase\n","final_save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv'\n","df_final.to_csv(final_save_path, index=False)\n","\n","print(f\"\\nSuccess! Your preprocessed dataset is saved at: {final_save_path}\")"],"metadata":{"id":"4Qb64sLW2p4q","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008626127,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":22970,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"2baafe80-a937-4765-80fd-68528510d34c","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Data Normalization Complete.\n","\n","Mean and Standard Deviation after scaling (should be ~0 and ~1):\n","ms_first_response_time    | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","past_attempts             | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","past_successes            | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","historical_accuracy       | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","item_difficulty           | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","gamification_score        | Mean: 0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","magic_hint_count          | Mean: -0.00 | Std: 1.00\n","\n","Success! Your preprocessed dataset is saved at: /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Etape 7 : la distribution du nombre d'interactions par utilisateur"],"metadata":{"id":"dq1QHsDvuTM2"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["crée un graphique pour analyser le comportement de vos étudiants. Il calcule combien d'exercices chaque élève a terminé, puis affiche une courbe (histogramme) pour voir si la majorité d'entre eux font beaucoup ou peu d'exercices. Cela vous permet de valider si votre choix technique de limiter les séquences à 50 interactions est bien adapté à la réalité de vos données avant de lancer l'entraînement de l'IA."],"metadata":{"id":"UawNK33DBOAE"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# 1. Calculate the number of interactions per student in the final dataset\n","interactions_per_student = df_final.groupby('user_id').size()\n","\n","# 2. Display descriptive statistics (Median, mean, percentiles)\n","print(\"--- Statistics of interactions per student ---\")\n","print(interactions_per_student.describe(percentiles=[0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.90, 0.95]))\n","\n","# 3. Plot an histogram to visualize the actual data distribution\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n","plt.hist(interactions_per_student, bins=50, range=(0, 200), color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')\n","\n","# Add vertical lines for the median and your current choice of 50\n","median_val = interactions_per_student.median()\n","plt.axvline(median_val, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_val}')\n","plt.axvline(50, color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Current Choice (MAX_SEQ_LEN): 50')\n","\n","plt.title(\"Distribution of the Number of Interactions per Student (Capped at 200)\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Number of Interactions (Exercises Completed)\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Students\")\n","plt.legend()\n","plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":695},"id":"R7e8ojO0sbxA","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008626793,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":664,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"d1a2c55b-209e-4ea7-b2bd-e5d2f2766538"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["--- Statistics of interactions per student ---\n","count    4437.000000\n","mean       44.773946\n","std        61.063055\n","min         1.000000\n","25%        10.000000\n","50%        23.000000\n","75%        54.000000\n","90%       113.000000\n","95%       168.200000\n","max       509.000000\n","dtype: float64\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ce graphique montre que la majorité de vos étudiants font relativement peu d'exercices, puisque la moitié d'entre eux en terminent moins de 23 (la ligne rouge). Votre limite fixée à 50 interactions (la ligne verte) est donc un très bon choix : elle permet à votre IA d'analyser le parcours complet de la grande majorité des élèves sans ralentir le système avec des calculs inutiles."],"metadata":{"id":"4GVDCcPICLkT"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 8:  Le Partitionnement Temporel (Temporal ou Chronological Split)**"],"metadata":{"id":"eIh01AdbYjGQ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ce code divise chronologiquement vos données en trois parties (60% pour l'apprentissage, 15% de contrôle, et 25% de test) pour d'abord apprendre à l'IA le comportement normal des étudiants, puis saboter volontairement un exercice dans le dernier bloc. Ces pourcentages sont stratégiques : ils donnent assez de passé à votre modèle pour devenir fiable, tout en vous réservant un grand espace \"futur\" pour injecter artificiellement cette fameuse dérive soudaine et vérifier si votre système est capable de sonner l'alarme."],"metadata":{"id":"CffEZFnRHaM6"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. LOAD AND SORT CHRONOLOGICALLY\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"Loading dataset...\")\n","df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/assistments_ready_for_model.csv')\n","\n","# Absolute rule: Sort by order_id to simulate the real passage of time\n","df = df.sort_values(by='order_id').reset_index(drop=True)\n","\n","total_interactions = len(df)\n","print(f\"Total interactions: {total_interactions}\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. CHRONOLOGICAL SPLIT (TIME-SPLIT)\n","# ==========================================\n","# Calculate cutoff indices for Train (60%), Baseline (15%), Drift (25%)\n","train_end_idx = int(total_interactions * 0.60)\n","baseline_end_idx = train_end_idx + int(total_interactions * 0.15)\n","\n","# Block A: The Past (60%) -> Used to train the AI\n","df_train = df.iloc[:train_end_idx].copy()\n","\n","# Block B: The Present (15%) -> Used to validate normal behavior (Baseline)\n","df_baseline = df.iloc[train_end_idx:baseline_end_idx].copy()\n","\n","# Block C: The Future (25%) -> Used as a laboratory for Concept Drift\n","df_drift = df.iloc[baseline_end_idx:].copy()\n","\n","print(\"\\nData splitting completed:\")\n","print(f\" - Train Block    : {len(df_train)} rows\")\n","print(f\" - Baseline Block : {len(df_baseline)} rows\")\n","print(f\" - Drift Block    : {len(df_drift)} rows\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","## ==========================================\n","# 3. CONCEPT DRIFT : DIFFICULTÉ D'ITEM MAL CALIBRÉE\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","# On cible les items de difficulté moyenne (entre 0.4 et 0.6) où l'élève avait réussi\n","mask_difficulty = (df_drift['item_difficulty'] >= 0.4) & \\\n","                  (df_drift['item_difficulty'] <= 0.6) & \\\n","                  (df_drift['correct'] == 1)\n","\n","# On sélectionne ces lignes (on peut prendre 100% pour un impact maximal)\n","infected_indices = df_drift[mask_difficulty].index\n","\n","# On transforme ces réussites en échecs\n","df_drift.loc[infected_indices, 'correct'] = 0\n","\n","# B. La conséquence métier : le score est puni injustement\n","# On annule la récompense (+10) et on applique la pénalité d'échec (-5) = -15\n","df_drift.loc[infected_indices, 'gamification_score'] -= 15\n","\n","# 4. Affichage du bilan pour ton suivi\n","print(f\"🚨 Dérive injectée avec succès sur {len(infected_indices)} interactions !\")\n","print(\" -> Les réponses sont passées à 0 (Échec).\")\n","print(\" -> Le score de gamification a été pénalisé de -15 points pour ces erreurs.\")\n","\n","# Affichage du bilan\n","print(f\"Injection massive : {len(infected_indices)} réussites sur des items 'moyens' sont devenues des échecs.\")\n","# Sauvegarder les trois blocs séparément sur Google Drive\n","chemin_dossier = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","df_train.to_csv(chemin_dossier + 'train_block.csv', index=False)\n","df_baseline.to_csv(chemin_dossier + 'baseline_block.csv', index=False)\n","df_drift.to_csv(chemin_dossier + 'drift_block.csv', index=False)\n","\n","print(\"Les 3 parties ont été sauvegardées avec succès !\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"5JRSxKwxY3k8","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008637662,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":10860,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"729eb225-98cf-466b-8883-096ddd82d057"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Loading dataset...\n","Total interactions: 198662\n","\n","Data splitting completed:\n"," - Train Block    : 119197 rows\n"," - Baseline Block : 29799 rows\n"," - Drift Block    : 49666 rows\n","🚨 Dérive injectée avec succès sur 2786 interactions !\n"," -> Les réponses sont passées à 0 (Échec).\n"," -> Le score de gamification a été pénalisé de -15 points pour ces erreurs.\n","Injection massive : 2786 réussites sur des items 'moyens' sont devenues des échecs.\n","Les 3 parties ont été sauvegardées avec succès !\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["**1. Est-ce que l'injection affecte l'ensemble des 25% du dataset ?**\n","Non, absolument pas. Dans le bloc des 25% (le futur), le code actuel fait ceci :\n","df_drift.loc[df_drift['problem_id'] == 15844, 'correct'] = 0\n","\n","Cela signifie que le sabotage est extrêmement isolé. Sur les milliers d'interactions contenues dans vos 25% de données futures, seules les quelques lignes concernant l'exercice précis n°15844 sont modifiées. Tout le reste du bloc \"Drift\" (les autres exercices, les autres compétences) reste parfaitement normal et sain.\n","\n","Le problème que cela crée : Un modèle comme le xLSTM est robuste. Si vous ne sabotez qu'un seul exercice sur des milliers, la métrique globale d'erreur (l'Accuracy ou l'AUC) ne bougera presque pas. Le modèle va \"noyer\" cette petite anomalie dans la masse de ses bonnes prédictions.\n","\n","C'est d'ailleurs exactement pour cette raison que, plus loin dans votre notebook, il y a eu cette tentative d'injecter une erreur massive de 40% directement sur les tenseurs : *l'injection de l'étape 7 était trop faible pour faire chuter les performances de l'IA.*\n","\n","Cependant, se limiter à une dérive soudaine n'est pas toujours réaliste pour évaluer un apprentissage continu. Dans la réalité de l'éducation, les concepts évoluent souvent via une dérive graduelle (Gradual Drift) : un concept devient lentement obsolète, ou les élèves changent progressivement de comportement au fil du semestre.\n","\n","**2. Pourquoi cette méthode d'injection n'est pas fiable (notamment pour l'explicabilité) ?**\n","Forcer manuellement correct = 0 sur un problem_id crée une dérive totalement artificielle et déconnectée du reste de vos données.\n","\n","Si vous appliquez ensuite des outils d'explicabilité (XAI) pour comprendre pourquoi le modèle s'est trompé, les explications n'auront aucun sens pédagogique. L'XAI dira : \"Le modèle a échoué parce que l'ID du problème est 15844\". Cela n'apporte aucune valeur analytique.\n","\n","Pour tester véritablement l'adaptation explicable d'un modèle d'apprentissage continu, la dérive doit être logique. Par exemple :\n","\n","Inverser la difficulté d'une compétence précise (ex: la géométrie devient soudainement très difficile pour tout le monde, modifiant la relation entre les tentatives passées et la réussite).\n","\n","Modifier l'impact d'une caractéristique (ex: le temps de réponse n'est plus corrélé à la réussite dans le bloc \"futur\")."],"metadata":{"id":"bGk77PapNKKG"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## **Etape 9 :Séquençage et Tensorisation **"],"metadata":{"id":"D1G3Sg_YueAU"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import torch\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 0. CHARGEMENT DES FICHIERS SAUVEGARDÉS\n","# ==========================================\n","load_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","print(\"Chargement des blocs depuis Google Drive...\")\n","\n","# On importe les 3 blocs que vous aviez sauvegardés à l'étape précédente\n","df_train = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'train_block.csv')\n","df_baseline = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'baseline_block.csv')\n","df_drift = pd.read_csv(load_path + 'drift_block.csv')\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. PARAMETERS & COLUMNS (CORRIGÉ)\n","# ==========================================\n","MAX_SEQ_LEN = 50\n","target_col = 'correct'\n","\n","# On ajoute TOUTES les colonnes non-numériques ici\n","cols_to_exclude = [\n","    'order_id', 'assignment_id', 'user_id', 'assistment_id',\n","    'problem_id', 'sequence_id', 'base_sequence_id', target_col,\n","    'list_skills'  # <--- C'est cette colonne qui bloquait tout !\n","]\n","\n","feature_cols = [col for col in df_train.columns if col not in cols_to_exclude]\n","print(f\"Nombre de caractéristiques injectées par séquence : {len(feature_cols)}\")\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. SEQUENCING FUNCTION (Padding/Truncating)\n","# ==========================================\n","def process_user_sequence(user_df):\n","    user_df = user_df.sort_values('order_id')\n","    x_user = user_df[feature_cols].values\n","    y_user = user_df[target_col].values\n","\n","    if len(x_user) > MAX_SEQ_LEN:\n","        x_user = x_user[-MAX_SEQ_LEN:]\n","        y_user = y_user[-MAX_SEQ_LEN:]\n","    elif len(x_user) < MAX_SEQ_LEN:\n","        pad_length = MAX_SEQ_LEN - len(x_user)\n","        pad_x = np.zeros((pad_length, len(feature_cols)))\n","        x_user = np.vstack((pad_x, x_user))\n","        pad_y = np.full((pad_length,), -1)\n","        y_user = np.concatenate((pad_y, y_user))\n","\n","    return x_user, y_user\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. ENCAPSULATION FOR TEMPORAL SEPARATION\n","# ==========================================\n","def dataframe_to_tensors(df_block, block_name):\n","    print(f\"\\nSéquençage du bloc : {block_name}...\")\n","    sequences = df_block.groupby('user_id').apply(process_user_sequence, include_groups=False)\n","\n","    X_3D = np.stack(sequences.apply(lambda x: x[0]).values)\n","    y_2D = np.stack(sequences.apply(lambda x: x[1]).values)\n","\n","    X_tensor = torch.tensor(X_3D, dtype=torch.float32)\n","    y_tensor = torch.tensor(y_2D, dtype=torch.float32)\n","\n","    print(f\"{block_name} terminé ! Shape X: {X_tensor.shape}, Shape y: {y_tensor.shape}\")\n","    return X_tensor, y_tensor\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. EXECUTION ET SAUVEGARDE\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n🚀 Démarrage de la tensorisation...\")\n","\n","X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_train, \"TRAIN\")\n","X_baseline_tensor, y_baseline_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_baseline, \"BASELINE\")\n","X_drift_tensor, y_drift_tensor = dataframe_to_tensors(df_drift, \"DRIFT\")\n","\n","# Sauvegarde des tenseurs prêts pour PyTorch\n","torch.save(X_train_tensor, load_path + 'X_train_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_train_tensor, load_path + 'y_train_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(X_baseline_tensor, load_path + 'X_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_baseline_tensor, load_path + 'y_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(X_drift_tensor, load_path + 'X_drift_tensor.pt')\n","torch.save(y_drift_tensor, load_path + 'y_drift_tensor.pt')\n","\n","print(f\"\\n✅ Tenseurs sauvegardés en sécurité dans : {load_path}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"FmKGEwtmucfo","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008647790,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":10102,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"74a2346d-0bf2-4890-c7d6-90df433c5dee"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Chargement des blocs depuis Google Drive...\n","Nombre de caractéristiques injectées par séquence : 18\n","\n","🚀 Démarrage de la tensorisation...\n","\n","Séquençage du bloc : TRAIN...\n","TRAIN terminé ! Shape X: torch.Size([3345, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([3345, 50])\n","\n","Séquençage du bloc : BASELINE...\n","BASELINE terminé ! Shape X: torch.Size([1642, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([1642, 50])\n","\n","Séquençage du bloc : DRIFT...\n","DRIFT terminé ! Shape X: torch.Size([2190, 50, 18]), Shape y: torch.Size([2190, 50])\n","\n","✅ Tenseurs sauvegardés en sécurité dans : /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Etape 9 : Entrainement (Train)"],"metadata":{"id":"X5153GyyE1B-"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import torch.optim as optim\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. STABILIZED xLSTM LAYER\n","# ==========================================\n","class xLSTMLayer(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(xLSTMLayer, self).__init__()\n","        self.hidden_size = hidden_size\n","        self.W = nn.Linear(input_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","        self.U = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 4 * hidden_size)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        batch_size, seq_len, _ = x.size()\n","        h = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","        c = torch.zeros(batch_size, self.hidden_size).to(x.device)\n","\n","        outputs = []\n","        for t in range(seq_len):\n","            xt = x[:, t, :]\n","            gates = self.W(xt) + self.U(h)\n","            i, f, o, g = gates.chunk(4, 1)\n","\n","            i = torch.exp(torch.clamp(i, max=20))\n","            f = torch.sigmoid(f)\n","            o = torch.sigmoid(o)\n","            g = torch.tanh(g)\n","\n","            c = f * c + i * g\n","            c = torch.clamp(c, min=-1e5, max=1e5)\n","\n","            h = o * torch.tanh(c)\n","            outputs.append(h.unsqueeze(1))\n","\n","        return torch.cat(outputs, dim=1)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. MODEL AND LOSS\n","# ==========================================\n","class KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):\n","        super(KnowledgeTracingxLSTM, self).__init__()\n","        self.xlstm = xLSTMLayer(input_size, hidden_size)\n","        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_size, 1)\n","\n","    def forward(self, x):\n","        out = self.xlstm(x)\n","        return self.fc(out).squeeze(-1)\n","\n","class MaskedBCELoss(nn.Module):\n","    def __init__(self):\n","        super(MaskedBCELoss, self).__init__()\n","        self.criterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss(reduction='none')\n","\n","    def forward(self, predictions, targets):\n","        loss = self.criterion(predictions, targets)\n","        mask = (targets != -1).float()\n","        return (loss * mask).sum() / (mask.sum() + 1e-8)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. PRÉPARATION DES DONNÉES (TRAIN UNIQUEMENT)\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","# Chargement exclusif du bloc Train (60%)\n","X_train_tensor = torch.load(save_path + 'X_train_tensor.pt')\n","y_train_tensor = torch.load(save_path + 'y_train_tensor.pt')\n","\n","BATCH_SIZE = 32\n","train_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_train_tensor, y_train_tensor), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n","\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=X_train_tensor.shape[2], hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","criterion = MaskedBCELoss()\n","optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.0005)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. ENTRAÎNEMENT PUR\n","# ==========================================\n","print(f\"🚀 Démarrage de l'entraînement exclusif sur {device}...\")\n","model.train()\n","\n","for epoch in range(10):\n","    total_loss = 0\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in train_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","\n","        optimizer.zero_grad()\n","        preds = model(X_batch)\n","        loss = criterion(preds, y_batch)\n","\n","        if torch.isnan(loss):\n","            continue\n","\n","        loss.backward()\n","        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)\n","        optimizer.step()\n","\n","        total_loss += loss.item()\n","\n","    avg_loss = total_loss / len(train_loader)\n","    print(f\"Epoch [{epoch+1}/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : {avg_loss:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Sauvegarde finale\n","torch.save(model.state_dict(), save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth')\n","print(f\"\\n✅ Modèle entraîné et sauvegardé avec succès dans : {save_path}reliable_xlstm_model.pth\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Q0XDlsFm54jg","outputId":"1554e521-b95c-4133-bcf4-7450992b6100","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008690179,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":42386,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["🚀 Démarrage de l'entraînement exclusif sur cpu...\n","Epoch [1/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.6070\n","Epoch [2/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.5075\n","Epoch [3/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.4588\n","Epoch [4/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.4261\n","Epoch [5/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3975\n","Epoch [6/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3829\n","Epoch [7/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3726\n","Epoch [8/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3639\n","Epoch [9/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3548\n","Epoch [10/10] | Loss d'apprentissage : 0.3478\n","\n","✅ Modèle entraîné et sauvegardé avec succès dans : /content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/reliable_xlstm_model.pth\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Etape 10 :l'Évaluation Baseline (les 15%)**"],"metadata":{"id":"Qv4icuyHEMrv"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import numpy as np\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, f1_score, roc_auc_score\n","import seaborn as sns\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. CHARGEMENT DU BLOC BASELINE UNIQUEMENT\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","print(\"📂 Chargement du tenseur Baseline...\")\n","X_baseline = torch.load(save_path + 'X_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","y_baseline = torch.load(save_path + 'y_baseline_tensor.pt')\n","\n","baseline_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_baseline, y_baseline), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. CHARGEMENT DU MODÈLE ET ÉVALUATION\n","# ==========================================\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=X_baseline.shape[2], hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth'))\n","model.eval()\n","\n","all_targets = []\n","all_probs = []\n","\n","with torch.no_grad():\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in baseline_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","        outputs = model(X_batch)\n","\n","        # Masque pour ignorer le padding (-1)\n","        mask = (y_batch != -1)\n","\n","        all_targets.extend(y_batch[mask].cpu().numpy())\n","        all_probs.extend(torch.sigmoid(outputs[mask]).cpu().numpy())\n","\n","# --- CALCUL DES MÉTRIQUES ---\n","targets = np.array(all_targets)\n","probs = np.array(all_probs)\n","preds = (probs > 0.5).astype(float)\n","\n","acc = (targets == preds).mean()\n","error_rate = 1 - acc\n","f1 = f1_score(targets, preds)\n","auc = roc_auc_score(targets, probs)\n","cm = confusion_matrix(targets, preds)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. AFFICHAGE DES RÉSULTATS\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*40)\n","print(\"📊 BILAN DE PERFORMANCE : BASELINE\")\n","print(\"=\"*40)\n","print(f\"✅ Précision (Accuracy) : {acc*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"❌ Taux d'Erreur        : {error_rate*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"🎯 F1-Score             : {f1:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"📈 AUC-ROC              : {auc:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Affichage de la Matrice de Confusion\n","plt.figure(figsize=(5,4))\n","sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Greens',\n","            xticklabels=['Échec (0)', 'Réussite (1)'],\n","            yticklabels=['Échec (0)', 'Réussite (1)'])\n","plt.title(\"Matrice de Confusion - Baseline\")\n","plt.ylabel('Réalité')\n","plt.xlabel('Prédiction')\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"_XpJWI-MEQZ4","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":567},"executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008691263,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":1082,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"c6708a66-8352-41b8-ed69-6a75cb4a3ba4"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["📂 Chargement du tenseur Baseline...\n","\n","========================================\n","📊 BILAN DE PERFORMANCE : BASELINE\n","========================================\n","✅ Précision (Accuracy) : 83.48%\n","❌ Taux d'Erreur        : 16.52%\n","🎯 F1-Score             : 0.8633\n","📈 AUC-ROC              : 0.8940\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 500x400 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Etape 11 : L'evaluation du bloc de dérive (Les 25%)"],"metadata":{"id":"73bzvmxPzDk-"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import torch\n","import torch.nn as nn\n","import numpy as np\n","from torch.utils.data import TensorDataset, DataLoader\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, f1_score, roc_auc_score\n","import seaborn as sns\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. CONFIGURATION & CHARGEMENT DU BLOC DRIFT\n","# ==========================================\n","device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n","save_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/DRIFT/Memoire_Data/'\n","\n","print(\"📂 Chargement du tenseur de dérive (DRIFT)...\")\n","X_drift = torch.load(save_path + 'X_drift_tensor.pt')\n","y_drift = torch.load(save_path + 'y_drift_tensor.pt')\n","\n","drift_loader = DataLoader(TensorDataset(X_drift, y_drift), batch_size=32, shuffle=False)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. CHARGEMENT DU MODÈLE ET PRÉDICTION\n","# ==========================================\n","# On récupère la dimension d'entrée dynamiquement (ex: 18 ou 19 features)\n","input_dim = X_drift.shape[2]\n","model = KnowledgeTracingxLSTM(input_size=input_dim, hidden_size=64).to(device)\n","model.load_state_dict(torch.load(save_path + 'reliable_xlstm_model.pth'))\n","model.eval()\n","\n","all_targets = []\n","all_probs = []\n","\n","print(\"🚀 Analyse du bloc de dérive en cours...\")\n","with torch.no_grad():\n","    for X_batch, y_batch in drift_loader:\n","        X_batch, y_batch = X_batch.to(device), y_batch.to(device)\n","        outputs = model(X_batch)\n","\n","        # Masque pour ignorer le padding (-1)\n","        mask = (y_batch != -1)\n","\n","        all_targets.extend(y_batch[mask].cpu().numpy())\n","        all_probs.extend(torch.sigmoid(outputs[mask]).cpu().numpy())\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. CALCUL DES MÉTRIQUES (ANOMALIES)\n","# ==========================================\n","targets = np.array(all_targets)\n","probs = np.array(all_probs)\n","preds = (probs > 0.5).astype(float)\n","\n","acc = (targets == preds).mean()\n","f1 = f1_score(targets, preds)\n","auc = roc_auc_score(targets, probs)\n","cm = confusion_matrix(targets, preds)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. AFFICHAGE DES RÉSULTATS (POUR LE MÉMOIRE)\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"!\"*45)\n","print(\"🚨 RÉSULTATS SUR LE BLOC DE DÉRIVE (DRIFT)\")\n","print(\"!\"*45)\n","print(f\"📉 Précision (Accuracy) : {acc*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"❌ Taux d'Erreur        : {error_rate*100:.2f}%\")\n","print(f\"🎯 F1-Score             : {f1:.4f}\")\n","print(f\"📈 AUC-ROC              : {auc:.4f}\")\n","\n","# Visualisation de la Matrice de Confusion\n","# On s'attend à voir beaucoup de Faux Positifs (le modèle prédit 1 mais c'est 0)\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))\n","sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Oranges',\n","            xticklabels=['Échec (0)', 'Réussite (1)'],\n","            yticklabels=['Échec (0)', 'Réussite (1)'])\n","plt.title(\"Matrice de Confusion - Bloc de Dérive\")\n","plt.ylabel('Réalité (Injectée)')\n","plt.xlabel('Prédiction (Modèle figé)')\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":662},"id":"5sv9r-W_z4wo","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773008692698,"user_tz":-60,"elapsed":1432,"user":{"displayName":"Oumaima Méchi","userId":"09875582261966675902"}},"outputId":"d85574ae-bfe0-4d5e-fa85-8a4fd3495683"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["📂 Chargement du tenseur de dérive (DRIFT)...\n","🚀 Analyse du bloc de dérive en cours...\n","\n","!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n","🚨 RÉSULTATS SUR LE BLOC DE DÉRIVE (DRIFT)\n","!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n","📉 Précision (Accuracy) : 83.57%\n","❌ Taux d'Erreur        : 16.52%\n","🎯 F1-Score             : 0.8552\n","📈 AUC-ROC              : 0.8924\n"]},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x500 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Etape 12:  Le Monitoring et la Double Alerte (Le Méta-Détecteur d'Ensemble)"],"metadata":{"id":"qzq3UDbUINKo"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Installation requise si ce n'est pas fait :\n","# !pip install river\n","\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","from river import drift\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. PRÉPARATION DES FLUX DE DONNÉES (DATA STREAMS)\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"🔄 Initialisation des capteurs du SIAD...\")\n","\n","# Flux 1 : Les erreurs du modèle xLSTM (0 = Correct, 1 = Erreur)\n","# (On suppose que 'targets' et 'preds' proviennent de ton évaluation précédente)\n","erreurs_modele = (targets != preds).astype(int)\n","\n","# Flux 2 : Le score de gamification (Métrique Métier)\n","# On prend les scores du bloc Drift de manière séquentielle\n","scores_metier = df_drift['gamification_score'].values\n","\n","# Pour synchroniser la simulation, on prend la longueur minimale\n","# (au cas où le séquençage xLSTM aurait légèrement tronqué les données)\n","stream_length = min(len(erreurs_modele), len(scores_metier))\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. INITIALISATION DES ALGORITHMES HAUTE PERFORMANCE\n","# ==========================================\n","# ADWIN pour les erreurs ML (détecte les changements de moyenne)\n","adwin_detector = drift.ADWIN()\n","\n","# KSWIN pour les scores (test statistique de Kolmogorov-Smirnov sur des valeurs continues)\n","# alpha = 0.005 contrôle la sensibilité (plus c'est bas, moins il y a de fausses alertes)\n","kswin_detector = drift.KSWIN(alpha=0.005, window_size=1000, stat_size=300)\n","\n","# Variables de mémorisation pour le tableau de bord\n","alertes_ml = []\n","alertes_metier = []\n","derives_majeures = []\n","\n","print(\"🚀 Lancement de la surveillance en temps réel (Streaming)...\\n\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. SIMULATION DU FLUX EN TEMPS RÉEL\n","# ==========================================\n","for i in range(stream_length):\n","    # 1. Lecture de la donnée à l'instant 'i'\n","    erreur_actuelle = erreurs_modele[i]\n","    score_actuel = scores_metier[i]\n","\n","    # 2. Mise à jour des algorithmes\n","    adwin_detector.update(erreur_actuelle)\n","    kswin_detector.update(score_actuel)\n","\n","    # 3. Vérification des alertes\n","    drift_ml = adwin_detector.drift_detected\n","    drift_metier = kswin_detector.drift_detected\n","\n","    # Enregistrement des alertes individuelles\n","    if drift_ml:\n","        alertes_ml.append(i)\n","    if drift_metier:\n","        alertes_metier.append(i)\n","\n","    # 4. LE CERVEAU DU SIAD : LA DOUBLE ALERTE\n","    # Si les deux algorithmes ont détecté une anomalie récemment (ex: dans une fenêtre de 500 interactions)\n","    if len(alertes_ml) > 0 and len(alertes_metier) > 0:\n","        dernier_ml = alertes_ml[-1]\n","        dernier_metier = alertes_metier[-1]\n","\n","        # S'ils sonnent presque en même temps (corrélation temporelle)\n","        if abs(dernier_ml - dernier_metier) < 500 and i not in derives_majeures:\n","            derives_majeures.append(i)\n","            print(f\"[{i}] 🚨 DÉRIVE CONCEPTUELLE MAJEURE CONFIRMÉE PAR LE SIAD !\")\n","            print(f\"    -> L'algorithme ADWIN a détecté une chute de l'Accuracy.\")\n","            print(f\"    -> L'algorithme KSWIN a détecté un effondrement des scores.\")\n","            print(f\"    -> Action : Gel des pénalités et appel de l'XAI.\\n\")\n","\n","            # Dans un vrai système, on pourrait stopper la boucle ici pour ré-entraîner.\n","            # Pour la simulation, on laisse tourner.\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 4. BILAN FINAL DE LA SURVEILLANCE\n","# ==========================================\n","print(\"=\"*50)\n","print(\"📊 RAPPORT FINAL DU DÉTECTEUR DE DÉRIVE (SIAD)\")\n","print(\"=\"*50)\n","print(f\"Total des interactions surveillées : {stream_length}\")\n","print(f\"-> Nombre d'alertes IA (ADWIN)     : {len(alertes_ml)}\")\n","print(f\"-> Nombre d'alertes Métier (KSWIN) : {len(alertes_metier)}\")\n","print(f\"-> DÉRIVES MAJEURES CONFIRMÉES     : {len(derives_majeures)}\")\n","\n","if len(derives_majeures) > 0:\n","    print(\"\\n✅ Le SIAD a parfaitement fonctionné : l'anomalie injectée a été captée par les deux systèmes de manière asynchrone puis corrélée.\")\n","else:\n"